      "date": "2025-08-26 14:17:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI attempted to fix the build errors present in this patch and succeeded. Yay! Now, keep in mind I barely have any idea what I am doing, so please doublecheck the changes I made to make sure they make sense.\n\nThis service is only provided in hopes to be useful and reduce latency from push to getting actual results in the face of trivial code errors\n\nHere's summary of my changes:\nThe changes made in this patch address a compile error caused by a mismatch between the function signature and its usage in `lnetctl.c`. Here's a summary:\n\n### Summary of Changes:\n- **Added a new variable `sen`**: A new `long int` variable `sen` (likely standing for \"sensitivity\" or similar) was introduced and initialized to `-1` alongside `hops` and `prio`.\n- **Updated function call parameters**: The calls to `yaml_lnet_router_gateways()` were modified to include the new `sen` parameter in both branches of the conditional logic (with and without `nid`).\n- **Initialized `sen` in the loop reset block**: The variable `sen` is now reset to `-1` at the end of the loop, consistent with `hops` and `prio`.\n\n### Purpose:\nThis change was necessary because the function `yaml_lnet_router_gateways()` was updated to accept an additional `sen` parameter (likely for router gateway sensitivity settings), but the previous code did not pass it. This resulted in a **compile error** due to a mismatch in the number of arguments.\n\n### Outcome:\nThe patch ensures that the function call matches the updated function signature, fixing the compile error while maintaining consistent initialization and logic flow.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
